# ExorLive Workout Exporter

ExorLive offers two solutions for exporting workouts:

The first solution is predominantly used for integration with journaling systems. The export is triggered automatically whenever the user signs a workout. Currently, we support automatic exports to journaling systems delivered by CGM, WebDoc, Tieto (Procapita, LifeCare), and PatientSky.
Please contact us if you would like to use this solution.

If you are not using any of the journaling systems named above you can use our API to export workouts. This solution can be used by any of our clients who purchased API access. It is up to the client to check whether there are any workouts eligible for export and request the PDF along with metadata.
Please see below for details.

## Steps

1. Get a list of workouts that are ready for export.

2. Download the PDF and some metadata about each workout.

3. Acknowledge when each workout has been received successfully.

## Signed workouts

When the user works with workouts in ExorLive they have the option to "sign" the workout. After it is signed it cannot easily be changed.
Typically the workout is signed when it is given to the contact/client, so it cannot be changed after that point.
The reason for the sign-functionality is that it should be clear exactly what exercises were given to the client. Therefore, the Workout Exporter API has the same requirement.

**Only signed workouts will be available to be exported through the API**.

Read more about signing workouts [here](https://support.exorlive.com/hc/en-gb/articles/360001418440-Sign-a-training-program).

## The endpoints

The endpoints expect a parameter "clientname", which should contain a agreed upon value. Contact ExorLive support to get assigned a clientname and get access to the API.
Also, each call expects two values in the HTTP header:

- "ExorLive-Client": The "clientname" to be agreed upon with ExorLive AS. The same value as the parameter.

- "Authorization": "Bearer accesstoken"

See the [authentication](/authentication.md) section about how to get the access token.

### GetAvailableWorkouts / GetAvailableWorkoutIds

Get a list of workouts that are ready for export.
There are two versions of this method. The first version returns some metadata for each workout. The other just returns the IDs of the workouts.

- clientname: The name of the application that is calling, as an agreed upon value. Discussed above.

- ownerId: The ExorLive user ID of the user that created the workouts to export. Use "0" (default) or omit it for all available users.

- contactId: The ExorLive user ID of the contact/client that may have some workouts to export. Use "0" (default) or omit it for all contacts.

- departmentId: The ExorLive department ID. Use this to filter on workouts from within a given department in your organization. Get applicable department IDs from ExorLive support. Use "0" (default) or omit it for the whole organization.

- scope: "new" (default) or "all". Use "new" to get only workouts that have not been exported/acknowledged previously.
